Use these classes for the main `container`.

 - `d-flex`: to make it flex
 - `flex-column`: to change its direction to `column`.
 - `h-100`: to give it a 100% height.


Use these classes for the main `row`.

 - `flex-grow-1` &amp; `flex-sm-grow-0`: to let it occupy all the available space on mobile only. Doing so, the footer is pushed at the very bottom of the page. If you want to have sticky footer on all the screen, irrespective of their viewport size, use &#242;nly `flex-grow-1` 


&lt;!-- begin snippet: js hide: false console: true babel: false --&gt;

&lt;!-- language: lang-html --&gt;

    &lt;link href=&quot;https://cdnjs.cloudflare.com/ajax/libs/twitter-bootstrap/4.1.3/css/bootstrap.min.css&quot; rel=&quot;stylesheet&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;div class=&quot;container d-flex flex-column h-100&quot;&gt;
      &lt;div class=&quot;row flex-grow-1 flex-sm-grow-0 &quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;col-md-6 col-md-offset-3 mob-horizontal mob-vertical&quot; style=&quot;margin-top: 5em;&quot;&gt;
          &lt;div class=&quot;panel-group text-sm-center&quot;&gt;
            &lt;div class=&quot;panel panel-info&quot;&gt;
              &lt;div class=&quot;panel-heading text-center&quot;&gt;/*content here*/&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class=&quot;panel-body mob-horizontal&quot;&gt;/*content here*/&lt;/div&gt;
              &lt;div class=&quot;panel-footer text-center&quot;&gt;/*content here*/&lt;/div&gt;
            &lt;/div&gt;
          &lt;/div&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;footer class=&quot;footer bg-danger&quot;&gt;
        &lt;div class=&quot;container&quot;&gt;
          &lt;span class=&quot;text-muted&quot;&gt;Place sticky footer content here.&lt;/span&gt;
        &lt;/div&gt;
      &lt;/footer&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;!-- end snippet --&gt;


----------

Both `html` and `body` must have 100% height. So use `h-100`.


----------

Their are a couple of ways to have sticky footer, [this answer](https://stackoverflow.com/questions/50674837/flush-footer-to-the-bottom-of-the-page-in-bootstrap-4/50678696#50678696) may be helpful too. 


Bootstrap has allso a similar footer. Visit [getbootstrap](https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.3/examples/sticky-footer-navbar/)

